1ï¸âƒ£ Types of Univariate Analysis
âœ… Descriptive Statistics (Numerical Summary)
It summarizes the main characteristics of the variable.

ğŸ“Œ Key Measures:

Mean (Average) â†’ Central tendency
Median â†’ Middle value
Mode â†’ Most frequent value
Variance & Standard Deviation â†’ Spread of data
Range & IQR â†’ Spread of extreme values
Example in Python:
python
Copy
Edit
import pandas as pd

# Sample data
data = {'Age': [22, 25, 30, 28, 32, 27, 40, 35, 22, 28]}
df = pd.DataFrame(data)

# Descriptive statistics
print(df.describe())
âœ… Key Takeaway: Useful for understanding summary statistics.

âœ… Frequency Distribution (Categorical Data)
ğŸ“Œ Used for categorical variables to count occurrences of each category.

Example in Python:
python
Copy
Edit
# Sample data
data = {'Department': ['HR', 'IT', 'IT', 'HR', 'Finance', 'HR', 'Finance', 'IT', 'IT', 'Finance']}
df = pd.DataFrame(data)

# Frequency distribution
print(df['Department'].value_counts())
âœ… Key Takeaway: Helps in understanding categorical variable distribution.

âœ… Visualization Techniques
1ï¸âƒ£ Histogram (Numerical Data)

Shows the distribution of a variable.
Best for continuous variables (e.g., salary, age).
python
Copy
Edit
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

df['Age'].plot(kind='hist', bins=5, edgecolor='black')
plt.title('Age Distribution')
plt.show()
2ï¸âƒ£ Boxplot (Outlier Detection)

Displays median, quartiles, and outliers.
python
Copy
Edit
df.boxplot(column=['Age'])
plt.show()
3ï¸âƒ£ Bar Plot (Categorical Data)

Shows frequency distribution.
python
Copy
Edit
df['Department'].value_counts().plot(kind='bar')
plt.show()
2ï¸âƒ£ When to Use Univariate Analysis?
âœ”ï¸ Understand Data Distribution
âœ”ï¸ Detect Outliers & Skewness
